for (i in 1:3) {

  cat("### ",i," \n")
  print( ggplot(iris,aes(y=Sepal.Length,x=Species))+ geom_boxplot()+ ggtitle(paste("plot",i)))
          plot.new()
  dev.off()

  cat(' \n\n')

}

  iris %>% 
      dplyr::group_split(Species) %>% 
      purrr::iwalk(.,~{
        # create tabset for each group 
        cat('### Tab',.y," \n")
        p <- ggplot(.x, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width)) + geom_point()
        print(p)
        cat(' \n\n')
      })
